                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120219-42-defend415 t18120219-42-deflabel252"></join>; the silver was taken off a knife case, the handle and the lock.</p>
               <p>Q. What age is the boy - A. He says himself he is more than fourteen.</p>
               <p>MR. SMART. I am a goldsmith. The prisoner offered me some silver for sale. It is the handles of a knife case, or of some furniture, he said his father was a broker; it was quite black; when he came the second time he brought a note, which he wrote himself, and signed his father's name. This is the silver.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. It is my silver, it fits the different parts of a knife case.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18120219-42-verdict253" type="verdictDescription">
